1
00:00:00,510 --> 00:00:02,210
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,210 --> 00:00:03,910
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:06,080 --> 00:00:08,750
My gosh, what's wrong with them?
What's their deal?

4
00:00:11,220 --> 00:00:13,350
- What? What's going on?
- Auntie.

5
00:00:14,250 --> 00:00:15,250
What?

6
00:00:16,920 --> 00:00:18,990
(Episode 9)

7
00:00:29,800 --> 00:00:31,540
What should we do?

8
00:00:46,790 --> 00:00:48,550
Do something, quick.

9
00:00:48,920 --> 00:00:52,160
- Let's get out and stop them.
- Okay.

10
00:01:00,900 --> 00:01:03,230
- That woman... Wait.
- What's wrong?

11
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:04,840
(Police)

12
00:01:09,970 --> 00:01:11,410
Hello, Ms. Yang.

13
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:14,480
- You scared me. What is it, Chief?
- Well...

14
00:01:14,550 --> 00:01:15,550
Hello.

15
00:01:16,650 --> 00:01:20,550
- What's going on?
- I'm sorry about last time.

16
00:01:20,650 --> 00:01:22,820
- Yes.
- You're sorry? For what?

17
00:01:23,720 --> 00:01:25,320
I'm a little busy right now.

18
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:28,630
- No! Wait!
- My goodness. Just a moment.

19
00:01:28,990 --> 00:01:30,730
I said I'm busy.
What do you think you're doing?

20
00:01:31,160 --> 00:01:33,160
It's just that...

21
00:01:33,970 --> 00:01:36,200
- If that's all, I'll be going now.
- No.

22
00:01:36,270 --> 00:01:37,640
I don't know
your circumstances, but...

23
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,640
- I really wanted to help you.
- Go!

24
00:01:40,310 --> 00:01:42,040
- But according to regulations,
- Excuse me?

25
00:01:42,510 --> 00:01:45,540
- we can't look up plates on a whim.
- Right.

26
00:01:45,610 --> 00:01:48,110
We've talked about this before.
You said you couldn't, right?

27
00:01:48,180 --> 00:01:49,480
You told me
to file an official report.

28
00:01:49,550 --> 00:01:52,150
Right. But we're still trying
to find a way, no matter what.

29
00:01:52,150 --> 00:01:54,390
- Go!
- We're trying everything we can.

30
00:01:54,450 --> 00:01:56,550
- Let's go.
- It's fine. Please step aside.

31
00:01:56,620 --> 00:01:57,660
- Ma'am...
- Wait.

32
00:01:57,790 --> 00:01:59,820
We're stepping up patrols
in the area.

33
00:02:00,230 --> 00:02:01,760
You haven't had any trouble,
have you?

34
00:02:02,390 --> 00:02:06,130
- No, none. Are we done here?
- Is that so?

35
00:02:07,430 --> 00:02:08,830
All right.
Thank you for your cooperation.

36
00:02:09,430 --> 00:02:11,470
- Take care now.
- Have a good day.

37
00:02:12,340 --> 00:02:13,610
(Police)

38
00:02:13,740 --> 00:02:15,040
What was that about? Seriously.

39
00:02:27,190 --> 00:02:28,190
Unbelievable.

40
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:30,120
I almost caught them.

41
00:02:53,010 --> 00:02:57,280
- That was a close call.
- I know. My heart's racing.

42
00:02:57,720 --> 00:02:59,750
Man, what would've happened
if we hadn't come by on our patrol?

43
00:02:59,820 --> 00:03:03,890
I know, right? But I thought
those two ran off together.

44
00:03:04,090 --> 00:03:05,760
What are they doing carrying on
like that here in Onjeong?

45
00:03:05,820 --> 00:03:07,260
That's what I'm saying.

46
00:03:07,630 --> 00:03:11,100
How can they be so bold
in broad daylight?

47
00:03:11,430 --> 00:03:14,700
- Unbelievable, really.
- Should we go back one last time?

48
00:03:16,970 --> 00:03:17,970
Hurry.

49
00:03:22,540 --> 00:03:25,540
Darling, the police helped us
on purpose, right?

50
00:03:25,610 --> 00:03:29,010
They did. It's like the heavens
are blessing our love.

51
00:03:35,490 --> 00:03:37,890
- Ju Ah.
- Hyun Bin.

52
00:03:38,220 --> 00:03:40,360
Love blessed by the heavens?
Give me a break.

53
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:42,990
If the heavens knew,
they'd strike you down.

54
00:03:47,270 --> 00:03:51,540
Look, I get that
people have affairs sometimes.

55
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:54,140
With another woman's husband,
a father.

56
00:03:54,570 --> 00:03:57,840
Fine. You make your own bed,
you lie in it. What do I care?

57
00:03:58,180 --> 00:04:02,650
- With that family of all people?
- Keep your voice down, will you?

58
00:04:03,150 --> 00:04:05,350
Do you have any idea how much
this is going to hurt our families?

59
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:09,320
Do you have no clue what will happen
if our fathers find out?

60
00:04:10,190 --> 00:04:13,660
I've already taken an earful from
my mother-in-law and sister-in-law.

61
00:04:14,430 --> 00:04:15,790
Grandma and Mom?

62
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:18,060
They know who
you're having an affair with?

63
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:20,700
Yes. Everyone knows but my husband.

64
00:04:23,170 --> 00:04:27,770
I agreed to take money for a divorce
and keep it from the families.

65
00:04:29,670 --> 00:04:32,140
So that's why
they offered you money.

66
00:04:33,010 --> 00:04:35,880
- Right.
- Then you should've left this town.

67
00:04:36,350 --> 00:04:39,550
Why make a scene in Onjeong
in public? What if you're seen?

68
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:42,550
His wife won't grant him a divorce.

69
00:04:43,150 --> 00:04:45,720
Yong Gil told me to go on to Ganghwa
and wait for him,

70
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:47,960
so we were just saying our goodbyes.

71
00:04:48,230 --> 00:04:49,460
Please.

72
00:04:49,830 --> 00:04:51,660
You're making me sick.
I can't listen to this anymore.

73
00:04:52,260 --> 00:04:53,900
To think my uncle called
a woman like you his wife.

74
00:04:55,970 --> 00:04:59,770
My poor uncle is the fool here,
treating you so delicately.

75
00:05:01,110 --> 00:05:02,170
Honestly.

76
00:05:12,650 --> 00:05:15,120
Didn't you know
she was from Dr. Gong's family?

77
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:18,390
Not at first, no.

78
00:05:19,460 --> 00:05:22,260
Once I found out,
I swear I tried to keep my distance.

79
00:05:23,390 --> 00:05:24,830
But the more I tried,

80
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:27,070
the more it felt like fate.

81
00:05:27,930 --> 00:05:29,530
Like we were Romeo and Juliet.

82
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:31,540
Don't you ever think about your son?

83
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:34,770
Ji Hu is all grown up.
He'll be fine with it.

84
00:05:35,670 --> 00:05:39,880
Hyun Bin, your parents got divorced
when you were his age, right?

85
00:05:40,310 --> 00:05:44,720
But look how well you turned out.
I hope Ji Hu looks up to you.

86
00:05:46,820 --> 00:05:47,990
This is so annoying.

87
00:05:50,860 --> 00:05:53,160
Does her family know about this?

88
00:05:54,030 --> 00:05:56,790
Well, the old lady at the pharmacy,

89
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:59,260
Dr. Han Seong Mi,

90
00:06:00,060 --> 00:06:01,530
and her son in med school
are probably the only ones.

91
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:06,800
Why did you meet
with Councilor Hwang?

92
00:06:07,340 --> 00:06:10,710
What did you say that made him
cancel the golf outing?

93
00:06:10,940 --> 00:06:14,010
You fool. Your problem is that
you always blame someone else.

94
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:17,550
How is this blaming someone else?
You're the one who blew a sure deal.

95
00:06:17,650 --> 00:06:21,550
Please. "A sure deal?"
It wasn't even close.

96
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:26,220
Councilor Hwang never even
considered you for the nomination.

97
00:06:27,090 --> 00:06:31,130
- Is that really true?
- Of course. Why would he pick you?

98
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:35,200
To a corner-cutter who pulls tricks
and even forges documents.

99
00:06:35,870 --> 00:06:39,470
See? I knew it. You went to him
and bad-mouthed me.

100
00:06:39,770 --> 00:06:40,940
What's your endgame here?

101
00:06:41,340 --> 00:06:43,540
Don't tell me you're after
my city council seat too.

102
00:06:43,810 --> 00:06:47,510
Hey. You're seriously paranoid.

103
00:06:47,580 --> 00:06:49,110
You should get
some professional help.

104
00:06:49,180 --> 00:06:53,280
Why do you think I'm like this?
You took everything from me.

105
00:06:53,380 --> 00:06:56,220
Hey. Since you brought it up,
let's settle this once and for all.

106
00:06:56,490 --> 00:06:58,260
What exactly
have I ever taken from you?

107
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:02,130
You got my father's vote
in exchange for treating him!

108
00:07:02,490 --> 00:07:03,560
What?

109
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,160
You've got to be kidding me.

110
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:09,470
Fine, whatever.
So what else did I take from you?

111
00:07:09,670 --> 00:07:13,500
You knew full well I liked Seong Mi,
but you dated her anyway.

112
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:17,740
No, you fool. You were the one
who liked my girlfriend.

113
00:07:17,810 --> 00:07:21,110
What about your dad seducing my mom
and running off with her?

114
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:25,920
You jerk. Are you spouting
any nonsense that comes to mind now?

115
00:07:25,980 --> 00:07:28,650
- Hey! Why are you fighting again?
- This is unbelievable.

116
00:07:28,650 --> 00:07:30,520
Let go! Talk it out!

117
00:07:30,960 --> 00:07:33,320
You're grown men.
Why are you still fighting this way?

118
00:07:33,660 --> 00:07:36,460
Why not? Then you might as well
take that video of me on my knees...

119
00:07:36,530 --> 00:07:37,900
and leak it to the whole town?

120
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:40,300
Go on, show everyone
how you used your power...

121
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:42,670
to make a desperate man kneel
and how you filmed it...

122
00:07:42,670 --> 00:07:45,070
to blackmail him.
Go ahead and play it for everyone!

123
00:07:45,670 --> 00:07:48,940
Because the only thing it'll do
is expose your true colors.

124
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,680
(Onjeong Market
Merchants' Association)

125
00:07:50,740 --> 00:07:51,740
That jerk...

126
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:55,750
No, wait. He's got a point.

127
00:07:56,510 --> 00:07:57,850
You really can't let that get out.

128
00:08:00,890 --> 00:08:05,620
Who's he to lecture me on character?
That jerk!

129
00:08:06,090 --> 00:08:07,120
Darn it.

130
00:08:08,290 --> 00:08:11,360
"Dr. Yang has a bad personality.
Basically, he's not very likable."

131
00:08:11,660 --> 00:08:12,860
That's what he said.

132
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:17,670
Oh, my.
That's a total misunderstanding.

133
00:08:17,870 --> 00:08:20,370
Someone is clearly trying
to slander him.

134
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:23,040
In any case, a full day of golf...

135
00:08:23,540 --> 00:08:25,340
He said it felt like
too much of a commitment.

136
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:29,650
A shame, after he worked so hard
to become the vice president.

137
00:08:31,320 --> 00:08:34,650
But you know
I'm not one to give up so easily.

138
00:08:35,350 --> 00:08:38,120
Please, could you put me in touch
with his wife?

139
00:08:38,860 --> 00:08:41,390
If you're uncomfortable
giving me her number,

140
00:08:41,690 --> 00:08:44,330
then just let me join you
next time you see her.

141
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:46,460
That might be a little difficult.

142
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:55,070
Atelier Vertige Eau de Toilette.

143
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:59,740
When I tried a sample of this,
I immediately thought of you.

144
00:09:00,180 --> 00:09:03,280
I'm having brunch with his wife
sometime this week.

145
00:09:03,410 --> 00:09:04,480
I'll let you know.

146
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:07,290
I'll be waiting for your call.

147
00:09:14,630 --> 00:09:15,860
What about the Cabanel bag?

148
00:09:16,190 --> 00:09:20,200
- I returned it to the rental place.
- What? Why did you send it back?

149
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:23,630
What do you mean, why?
It was rented, so I returned it.

150
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:28,040
But you got money from Grandfather!
You could've paid it off...

151
00:09:28,110 --> 00:09:30,040
and just kept the bag!

152
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:32,510
It's limited-edition.
You know it's hard to find!

153
00:09:32,580 --> 00:09:37,080
Gosh, listen, I have a bad headache.
Let's drop it for now, sweetie.

154
00:09:37,280 --> 00:09:39,250
Would you treat me like this
if I were your real daughter?

155
00:09:39,350 --> 00:09:42,150
- Yes, I would.
- Liar!

156
00:09:42,620 --> 00:09:44,720
- You're done talking, right?
- Wait!

157
00:09:44,790 --> 00:09:45,790
Se Ri!

158
00:09:47,160 --> 00:09:49,560
Se Ri, wait! I need to talk to you.
Just for a second.

159
00:09:51,030 --> 00:09:52,830
Gosh, that Cabanel bag...

160
00:09:53,970 --> 00:09:57,170
My goodness. So?
Did you see the woman's face?

161
00:09:57,370 --> 00:10:00,810
No, I only saw her from behind.
A police car blocked my view.

162
00:10:01,140 --> 00:10:03,310
If they met at the playground
right after the call...

163
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:07,010
- She must be from Onjeong.
- Who in the world could it be?

164
00:10:07,610 --> 00:10:09,710
Could it be some woman
he met near work?

165
00:10:10,180 --> 00:10:13,720
Now we know she's from Onjeong,
I'll have my people identify her.

166
00:10:15,350 --> 00:10:17,920
If I ever get my hands
on that witch,

167
00:10:18,490 --> 00:10:19,920
I'm going to tear her life apart.

168
00:10:22,390 --> 00:10:23,790
Darling, did you get home safe?

169
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:26,800
Just wait a little longer.
I'll get a divorce and come to you.

170
00:10:34,910 --> 00:10:36,340
I have something to tell you.

171
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:39,880
I'm seeing someone else.

172
00:10:41,050 --> 00:10:42,110
So what?

173
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:43,950
I want a divorce!

174
00:10:44,020 --> 00:10:46,450
How dare you ask for a divorce
when you're the one who cheated?

175
00:10:46,950 --> 00:10:49,750
Dong Suk, please just let me go.

176
00:10:49,820 --> 00:10:51,990
You don't love me either.

177
00:10:52,620 --> 00:10:53,790
Who is this witch?

178
00:10:54,430 --> 00:10:57,460
- Why do you need to know?
- I'm going to sue her for adultery.

179
00:10:57,460 --> 00:10:58,560
What?

180
00:10:58,560 --> 00:11:02,230
She has to pay the price
for wrecking a family, right?

181
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:11,010
Darn it.

182
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:17,780
- Gong Woo Jae.
- You scared me. You should knock.

183
00:11:17,850 --> 00:11:21,920
Why didn't you say our aunt's lover
is from Dr. Yang's clinic?

184
00:11:22,990 --> 00:11:24,690
How did you find that out?

185
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:27,990
How do you think I found out?
I saw them in daylight, so close...

186
00:11:28,190 --> 00:11:31,630
- Getting all handsy. Gosh, really.
- What?

187
00:11:32,460 --> 00:11:34,970
Hui Gyeong is still in Onjeong?

188
00:11:36,830 --> 00:11:39,370
It's a huge relief that you saw them
and not his family.

189
00:11:39,570 --> 00:11:41,640
I wasn't alone.
I was with the Director.

190
00:11:42,170 --> 00:11:44,380
The Director? You mean Bucket's son?

191
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:46,980
Yes. He was visiting his family.

192
00:11:46,980 --> 00:11:48,850
We were in his car together
when we saw them.

193
00:11:49,350 --> 00:11:52,180
He called me and said he'd handle it
so it doesn't blow up.

194
00:11:52,220 --> 00:11:56,750
It can't get out of hand.
If the dads find out, it'll be war.

195
00:11:57,250 --> 00:12:00,960
- So only Dad and Uncle don't know?
- Right.

196
00:12:01,030 --> 00:12:03,260
Darn it. What the...
Guys, you scared me.

197
00:12:03,630 --> 00:12:05,360
What's everyone doing in my room?

198
00:12:05,430 --> 00:12:08,000
Does anyone here ever knock?
Seriously.

199
00:12:08,130 --> 00:12:10,530
Why would I knock
to come into my own room?

200
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:11,940
Why did you come home so early?

201
00:12:11,940 --> 00:12:13,440
You said the association
was keeping you busy.

202
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:16,270
He got into a huge fight
with Bucket.

203
00:12:16,340 --> 00:12:19,640
- They fought? But why?
- Is there a family problem?

204
00:12:19,740 --> 00:12:21,880
Just because I met
with Councilor Hwang,

205
00:12:21,880 --> 00:12:24,520
that jerk had a huge fit.

206
00:12:27,690 --> 00:12:30,690
- I have to go somewhere.
- Me too.

207
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:32,390
- Hey, wait.
- Oh, I wonder what Mother is up to.

208
00:12:32,390 --> 00:12:34,090
- Hear me out. Hey!
- Mother!

209
00:12:34,090 --> 00:12:36,090
This is so unfair, I can't even...
I'm so furious...

210
00:12:37,090 --> 00:12:40,930
- Gosh, I can't believe this.
- It's okay. I've got your back.

211
00:12:41,930 --> 00:12:43,800
You saw the whole thing, didn't you?

212
00:12:45,140 --> 00:12:47,910
He looked utterly flustered
when I said that.

213
00:12:48,410 --> 00:12:50,670
You really should have seen
the look on his face.

214
00:12:50,770 --> 00:12:53,740
Darling, you're so clever.

215
00:12:53,880 --> 00:12:56,310
I thought
the video of you kneeling...

216
00:12:56,310 --> 00:12:58,850
would only put you
at a disadvantage.

217
00:12:59,350 --> 00:13:02,720
I guess I'm just a fool
who can't see the big picture.

218
00:13:03,890 --> 00:13:06,760
Have you tried getting in touch
with Councilor Hwang's people again?

219
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:08,430
Why did he cancel the golf outing?

220
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:13,900
- Well, he had a headache.
- What a shame.

221
00:13:14,570 --> 00:13:17,800
He was very apologetic
and insisted we reschedule.

222
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:20,570
This won't affect our special plan
whatsoever.

223
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:22,410
It's just a tiny little hiccup,

224
00:13:22,670 --> 00:13:23,870
so let's not overreact.

225
00:13:23,870 --> 00:13:26,540
Save this golf outfit
for another day.

226
00:13:27,950 --> 00:13:28,950
Is that right?

227
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:31,650
You think I was too hard
on Jeong Han?

228
00:13:31,750 --> 00:13:36,120
No, you did the right thing, honey.
He needs a reminder of his place.

229
00:13:36,620 --> 00:13:37,690
That's true.

230
00:13:39,160 --> 00:13:41,490
My, it's Hyun Bin.

231
00:13:43,530 --> 00:13:44,560
Son.

232
00:13:45,460 --> 00:13:48,470
You should've just come home.
Why did you want to meet out here?

233
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:52,970
Earlier, near our house,

234
00:13:53,770 --> 00:13:55,310
I saw Uncle.

235
00:13:57,270 --> 00:13:58,280
Oh, wait...

236
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:02,110
With another woman?

237
00:14:02,650 --> 00:14:04,150
So you already knew.

238
00:14:06,450 --> 00:14:07,520
By any chance...

239
00:14:08,550 --> 00:14:09,790
Did you see who she was?

240
00:14:13,860 --> 00:14:15,530
It was Uncle Dae Han's wife.

241
00:14:16,290 --> 00:14:17,290
Who?

242
00:14:17,830 --> 00:14:18,830
The one from the clinic.

243
00:14:23,230 --> 00:14:24,240
My gosh!

244
00:14:25,100 --> 00:14:26,100
I can't believe it.

245
00:14:26,700 --> 00:14:27,970
Her? That ditzy woman?

246
00:14:28,370 --> 00:14:31,410
My goodness. No way.
How could he possibly be with her?

247
00:14:31,510 --> 00:14:33,040
What are we going to do?
This is unbelievable.

248
00:14:34,310 --> 00:14:35,780
What about her husband?

249
00:14:36,310 --> 00:14:37,480
Does that family know?

250
00:14:38,150 --> 00:14:41,220
According to Uncle,
the pharmacist and Dr. Han...

251
00:14:41,390 --> 00:14:42,850
went all the way to Ganghwa
to see them.

252
00:14:44,460 --> 00:14:45,560
Ganghwa?

253
00:14:45,790 --> 00:14:48,490
Doctor, what brings you here?

254
00:14:50,290 --> 00:14:52,160
The public health center here...

255
00:14:52,830 --> 00:14:55,730
asked me to run
a mental health program.

256
00:14:57,370 --> 00:14:59,000
I'm just speechless.

257
00:14:59,570 --> 00:15:02,310
How could she lie
so brazenly like that?

258
00:15:02,540 --> 00:15:04,980
Maybe she just didn't want us
to find out.

259
00:15:05,410 --> 00:15:07,780
Apparently, Uncle Dae Han
and Dr. Gong don't know either.

260
00:15:09,310 --> 00:15:11,120
That's a relief, at least.

261
00:15:12,650 --> 00:15:14,250
Anyway, son...

262
00:15:15,150 --> 00:15:17,390
You absolutely did the right thing
by telling me.

263
00:15:18,490 --> 00:15:19,820
What are you going to do?

264
00:15:20,020 --> 00:15:22,330
I'll have to end this quietly.
Without a soul finding out.

265
00:15:22,730 --> 00:15:25,030
Absolutely no one can know
about this.

266
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:27,230
If your grandfather, father,
and aunt were to find out,

267
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:29,470
can you imagine
how devastated they would be?

268
00:15:30,230 --> 00:15:33,740
I'm sorry for dumping this on you
when I can't even fix it myself.

269
00:15:33,840 --> 00:15:36,040
What? Don't say that.

270
00:15:37,010 --> 00:15:38,540
As the lady of the Yang house,

271
00:15:38,840 --> 00:15:40,680
it's my responsibility
to handle these things.

272
00:15:41,310 --> 00:15:43,950
I'm so grateful to you,
for so many reasons.

273
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:47,180
Hey, then...

274
00:15:48,620 --> 00:15:51,890
Could I ask you for a favor?

275
00:15:53,190 --> 00:15:54,490
Yes, of course. Anything.

276
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:05,300
Thank you.
I didn't even realize I left it.

277
00:16:05,640 --> 00:16:08,770
- What happened?
- I told her to leave for good.

278
00:16:09,070 --> 00:16:13,140
- What about you?
- I asked my stepmother for help.

279
00:16:13,740 --> 00:16:15,650
Are you sure that was a good idea?

280
00:16:16,110 --> 00:16:18,980
She'll handle it.
She's the person I trust the most.

281
00:16:19,620 --> 00:16:20,620
Okay.

282
00:16:21,620 --> 00:16:25,290
Should we get back
to where we left off?

283
00:16:27,460 --> 00:16:30,190
Well... Where were we again?

284
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:33,460
Right. That you hate the idea of me
on a blind date,

285
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:36,930
and you can't stand seeing me smile
at other guys.

286
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:38,570
That's as far as you got.

287
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:41,940
When I was in Argentina,

288
00:16:42,340 --> 00:16:44,010
do you know why
I never got in touch?

289
00:16:45,010 --> 00:16:48,650
I just figured you'd met
some pretty blonde girl.

290
00:16:52,850 --> 00:16:54,450
I didn't have the confidence.

291
00:16:55,490 --> 00:16:58,790
I didn't think
there was a future for us.

292
00:17:00,090 --> 00:17:01,090
A future?

293
00:17:01,390 --> 00:17:04,190
Wait, you were already thinking
about a future back then?

294
00:17:04,760 --> 00:17:05,760
I was.

295
00:17:06,630 --> 00:17:10,570
What kind of house we'd live in,
whether to have a son or a daughter.

296
00:17:10,970 --> 00:17:12,840
Oh, my goodness.

297
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:14,440
Isn't that a given?

298
00:17:14,770 --> 00:17:17,570
When you're in love,
you naturally want to be together.

299
00:17:17,570 --> 00:17:18,740
You dream about
getting married, having kids,

300
00:17:18,740 --> 00:17:20,480
and building
a happy future together.

301
00:17:20,910 --> 00:17:23,850
Well, I guess that's true, but...

302
00:17:25,720 --> 00:17:26,780
But...

303
00:17:28,220 --> 00:17:32,120
Back then,
I was so ashamed of my family.

304
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:34,460
With a family
that even I couldn't stand,

305
00:17:34,860 --> 00:17:37,530
I just couldn't bring myself
to ask you to be a part of them.

306
00:17:42,370 --> 00:17:45,940
Earlier,
my stepmother asked me for a favor.

307
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:49,710
My grandfather and father
had a fight,

308
00:17:50,140 --> 00:17:52,380
and she asked me
to help them make up.

309
00:17:54,010 --> 00:17:57,680
Normally, I'd hate the thought
of doing that, but I agreed to help.

310
00:17:58,480 --> 00:18:00,680
This family of mine
that I'm so ashamed of...

311
00:18:01,450 --> 00:18:03,490
I've decided I want to try
and change them.

312
00:18:05,020 --> 00:18:09,260
I'm going to rebrand my family.
For you, Gong Ju Ah.

313
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:14,830
You showed up right in front of me
when I got back to Korea,

314
00:18:15,130 --> 00:18:18,370
and we ended up at the same company.
I think it's all destiny.

315
00:18:19,670 --> 00:18:21,940
I've been trying to deny it
and run from it,

316
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:25,740
but I can't hide
my feelings anymore.

317
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:30,580
It's a fact that
our families despise each other,

318
00:18:31,250 --> 00:18:34,720
but I'm going to try to overcome it,
if you're okay with that.

319
00:18:36,920 --> 00:18:39,520
No, I mean... It's just...

320
00:18:39,560 --> 00:18:42,630
I've never thought about
anything like this before.

321
00:18:42,790 --> 00:18:45,560
I know this is sudden.
And I know it's a lot to take in.

322
00:18:46,030 --> 00:18:48,570
Take all the time you need
to think about it.

323
00:18:52,500 --> 00:18:56,040
And I prepared this earlier today.

324
00:18:57,070 --> 00:18:58,110
Please give this to your uncle.

325
00:18:59,240 --> 00:19:00,410
My gosh.

326
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:16,290
You should have some, too.

327
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:22,730
If you don't eat well while dieting,
you'll lose muscle,

328
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:23,970
your metabolic hormones
will be imbalanced,

329
00:19:24,030 --> 00:19:25,300
and it can weaken
your immune system.

330
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:30,910
You sound like a real doctor.
It's so cool.

331
00:19:32,340 --> 00:19:34,680
Do you only like me
because I'm going to be a doctor?

332
00:19:34,750 --> 00:19:37,680
Or are you pretending to like me
to get on your stepmom's nerves?

333
00:19:42,250 --> 00:19:44,590
What's your first-ever memory?

334
00:19:45,320 --> 00:19:46,860
- Out of the blue?
- Yes.

335
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:51,730
I remember...

336
00:19:52,260 --> 00:19:56,500
I was five? I got hit by a ball
watching older kids play.

337
00:20:00,270 --> 00:20:02,810
Mine's from first grade,

338
00:20:03,570 --> 00:20:05,310
on a drizzly spring day.

339
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:08,910
I put on my raincoat to go to school
and stepped outside,

340
00:20:08,980 --> 00:20:12,450
and there was this giant earthworm
right in front of the gate.

341
00:20:12,950 --> 00:20:16,790
It was so gross and scary,
I was frozen in place,

342
00:20:17,550 --> 00:20:19,120
but the boy
from across the street...

343
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:21,360
moved it to the flowerbed
with a stick.

344
00:20:22,330 --> 00:20:23,760
I did that?

345
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:27,130
Yes. You saved both of us,
the earthworm and me.

346
00:20:28,530 --> 00:20:31,500
I fell for that kind-hearted boy
from the very beginning.

347
00:20:31,870 --> 00:20:35,310
So I don't care what you become.

348
00:20:36,540 --> 00:20:40,010
Although, it is pretty fun
that my stepmom hates it.

349
00:20:41,850 --> 00:20:45,080
If I fail again, I can't put it off.
I'll have to enlist in the army.

350
00:20:46,650 --> 00:20:50,150
But I've always romanticized
waiting for a boyfriend in the army.

351
00:20:56,290 --> 00:20:57,690
- Dad.
- Oh, there you are.

352
00:20:58,860 --> 00:20:59,860
Have you eaten?

353
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:02,170
Gosh, it's cold.

354
00:21:02,170 --> 00:21:03,170
(Junghu Academy)

355
00:21:06,370 --> 00:21:07,370
Dong Suk.

356
00:21:08,170 --> 00:21:11,110
The reason you don't want a divorce.
It's because of Ji Hu, isn't it?

357
00:21:12,410 --> 00:21:13,580
That's right.

358
00:21:14,140 --> 00:21:15,550
Is there any other reason?

359
00:21:16,010 --> 00:21:19,880
No. I'm completely fed up
with that man.

360
00:21:21,150 --> 00:21:23,290
Then stop torturing yourself...

361
00:21:24,220 --> 00:21:25,560
and divorce him.

362
00:21:26,820 --> 00:21:27,860
But...

363
00:21:30,030 --> 00:21:31,760
how am I supposed to raise Ji Hu
on my own?

364
00:21:32,430 --> 00:21:36,430
What do you mean, on your own?
We're all here to support you.

365
00:21:38,140 --> 00:21:42,810
You want Ji Hu to be a great doctor
and inherit our clinic, right?

366
00:21:46,040 --> 00:21:47,540
I will personally make sure...

367
00:21:48,510 --> 00:21:50,880
that Ji Hu grows up to be the man
you want him to be.

368
00:21:52,580 --> 00:21:55,050
- Se Ri.
- So please, just...

369
00:21:55,620 --> 00:21:57,620
get off this sinking ship.

370
00:22:05,460 --> 00:22:06,600
Oh, Mom!

371
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:09,200
- Hey.
- Hello, ma'am.

372
00:22:09,230 --> 00:22:10,230
See you.

373
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:22,280
You must be hungry. Go on, eat up.

374
00:22:27,050 --> 00:22:28,220
Eat up.

375
00:22:36,290 --> 00:22:37,290
Ji Hu.

376
00:22:39,060 --> 00:22:40,430
I...

377
00:22:43,130 --> 00:22:45,040
have something to tell you.

378
00:22:46,540 --> 00:22:47,670
Divorce Dad.

379
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:50,470
I'm okay with it.

380
00:22:51,980 --> 00:22:54,980
You knew this whole time?

381
00:22:55,610 --> 00:22:57,280
Don't stay in this marriage
for my sake.

382
00:22:58,150 --> 00:23:00,980
If you do,
we'll all just be miserable.

383
00:23:02,390 --> 00:23:04,490
A lot of kids in my class
have divorced parents.

384
00:23:05,160 --> 00:23:06,190
Nowadays,

385
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:08,560
kids don't get teased
for that anymore.

386
00:23:09,760 --> 00:23:10,860
Don't worry about me.

387
00:23:14,430 --> 00:23:16,630
My boy, you're all grown up.

388
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:19,640
I feel like
I haven't done anything for you.

389
00:23:24,710 --> 00:23:25,940
You should eat something too, Mom.

390
00:23:26,480 --> 00:23:28,150
You've been looking so drained
lately.

391
00:23:32,950 --> 00:23:33,950
Okay, let's eat.

392
00:23:42,860 --> 00:23:44,130
What did you just say?

393
00:23:44,460 --> 00:23:46,360
You're saying
Bucket's wife found out everything?

394
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:49,630
Hush. He said it's the only way
to resolve things over there.

395
00:23:50,100 --> 00:23:51,100
I suppose so.

396
00:23:52,900 --> 00:23:54,640
Anyway, this is so draining.

397
00:23:55,240 --> 00:23:58,940
When I ran into her in Ganghwa,
I had to lie to cover things up,

398
00:23:59,180 --> 00:24:00,840
and now this is going to come back
to bite me.

399
00:24:01,010 --> 00:24:05,220
- No, I'm sure she'll understand.
- What?

400
00:24:05,520 --> 00:24:06,620
Are you taking her side now?

401
00:24:13,020 --> 00:24:16,260
Wow, so this is
what you were out buying all day?

402
00:24:16,860 --> 00:24:19,060
Gosh, I feel so much better
now that it's replaced.

403
00:24:19,560 --> 00:24:22,300
If I had it my way,
I'd replace all the furniture too.

404
00:24:22,730 --> 00:24:26,800
Mom, what's wrong with it?
It's still good. It'd be a waste.

405
00:24:26,870 --> 00:24:28,670
He's right.
Mom, let's keep the furniture.

406
00:24:29,010 --> 00:24:30,870
I'll clean it all up
and make it look brand new.

407
00:24:31,210 --> 00:24:32,210
All right!

408
00:24:49,990 --> 00:24:53,530
Oh, what's this cake for?
Wow, this looks expensive.

409
00:24:53,660 --> 00:24:56,200
I bought it from the hotel
for you, Uncle.

410
00:24:56,770 --> 00:24:59,400
Wow, that's my girl, Ju Ah.

411
00:25:00,400 --> 00:25:03,810
This is a party
to celebrate your divorce!

412
00:25:05,810 --> 00:25:08,780
Hey, Ju Ah.
You're really something else.

413
00:25:08,850 --> 00:25:13,120
We should celebrate his new start
and his choice to be happier.

414
00:25:13,180 --> 00:25:15,990
That's right.
What's not to celebrate?

415
00:25:16,050 --> 00:25:18,460
Come on, let's all be cool
about this, okay?

416
00:25:18,460 --> 00:25:19,460
Yes, Mother.

417
00:25:19,460 --> 00:25:20,620
- I like the idea of being cool.
- Yes.

418
00:25:20,690 --> 00:25:22,330
Good job, sweetie.
Go on, light the candles.

419
00:25:23,060 --> 00:25:25,630
Uncle, once you blow these out...

420
00:25:25,700 --> 00:25:28,060
There! All your troubles
will just disappear.

421
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:29,970
- Just a moment. Goodness.
- That's right.

422
00:25:30,030 --> 00:25:32,670
- I'll blow them out. Thank you.
- Yes.

423
00:25:38,910 --> 00:25:40,910
But Dae Han,

424
00:25:41,410 --> 00:25:44,080
aren't you curious
who she had the affair with?

425
00:25:44,150 --> 00:25:45,980
- Why would he be curious?
- Hey!

426
00:25:46,480 --> 00:25:48,990
Do you always have to be
such a buzzkill?

427
00:25:49,520 --> 00:25:54,160
- What? I thought this was cool.
- That's not what being cool means.

428
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:56,430
- Stop talking nonsense. Goodness.
- Exactly.

429
00:25:56,490 --> 00:25:59,730
Seriously, why is everyone
always ganging up on me? My gosh.

430
00:26:00,030 --> 00:26:03,800
Hey, Dae Han,
why don't you go on a trip?

431
00:26:04,470 --> 00:26:07,440
- For a change of scenery.
- No, the clinic's busy, so I can't.

432
00:26:07,500 --> 00:26:10,070
- No, you should go. Just go.
- No, it's not that, Jeong Han.

433
00:26:10,670 --> 00:26:13,540
I'm not just pretending to be okay.
I'm really fine.

434
00:26:14,040 --> 00:26:17,610
I'm sorry and a little embarrassed
that I made you all worry,

435
00:26:18,250 --> 00:26:21,890
but I'm so grateful that
you're all looking out for me.

436
00:26:21,950 --> 00:26:25,120
And because I have all of you,
I'll be fine. Okay?

437
00:26:25,760 --> 00:26:30,190
Uncle, if you don't want a trip...
Ta-da! How about a concert?

438
00:26:30,360 --> 00:26:31,360
Here you go.

439
00:26:32,130 --> 00:26:33,160
What's this?

440
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:35,230
Let's see.

441
00:26:36,630 --> 00:26:37,870
Wow, awesome!

442
00:26:38,440 --> 00:26:40,240
Tickets to a 70s and 80s concert.

443
00:26:40,300 --> 00:26:42,710
- Nice.
- What? Hey, there are two tickets.

444
00:26:42,710 --> 00:26:43,970
Who are you going to take?

445
00:26:44,040 --> 00:26:46,610
Well... Mom?

446
00:26:49,680 --> 00:26:53,480
Please. Count me out.
Jeong Han is pouting. You two go.

447
00:26:53,550 --> 00:26:56,420
No, Mom. Look, your favorite singer,
Yeo Jin, is in it.

448
00:26:56,490 --> 00:26:58,220
- He's right, Mom.
- Really?

449
00:26:58,290 --> 00:26:59,290
Yes, here. Look.

450
00:27:00,720 --> 00:27:04,460
<i>- My darling love, once so kind</i>
<i>- Once so kind</i>

451
00:27:04,530 --> 00:27:07,700
<i>- Have you forgotten me?</i>
<i>- Have you forgotten me?</i>

452
00:27:08,060 --> 00:27:13,270
<i>- Have you already forgotten me?</i>
<i>- Have you already forgotten me?</i>

453
00:27:14,640 --> 00:27:15,810
- Hey. Let's eat!
- Yes, let's eat.

454
00:27:16,440 --> 00:27:17,910
- Yes, let's eat.
- We're eating now?

455
00:27:17,970 --> 00:27:18,980
- Take out the candle.
- All right.

456
00:27:19,040 --> 00:27:21,410
Hey. How did you even think of that?

457
00:27:21,580 --> 00:27:24,080
I know, right? How thoughtful.

458
00:27:24,650 --> 00:27:26,120
Hey, give it here. It's my cake.

459
00:27:34,290 --> 00:27:35,530
What is this?

460
00:27:38,030 --> 00:27:39,400
It's yerba mate.

461
00:27:39,600 --> 00:27:43,430
In Argentina, families share mate
and drink from the same straw.

462
00:27:43,800 --> 00:27:46,070
It's a tradition
that signifies trust and intimacy.

463
00:27:48,570 --> 00:27:53,340
I hoped by sharing this,
you two could mend things.

464
00:27:54,610 --> 00:27:57,510
This will all blow over in time.
You're being dramatic.

465
00:27:58,680 --> 00:28:00,120
All right, starting now.

466
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:02,790
Hear each other out
as you talk about what hurt you.

467
00:28:02,790 --> 00:28:04,850
Then take a sip of yerba mate...

468
00:28:04,920 --> 00:28:07,660
and say,
"I see. So that's how you felt."

469
00:28:07,720 --> 00:28:09,460
All right, Dad, you can start!

470
00:28:14,260 --> 00:28:15,270
Go on.

471
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:19,000
When I...

472
00:28:19,570 --> 00:28:21,070
was preparing for the election,

473
00:28:21,700 --> 00:28:24,910
- you know how hard I worked.
- Eye contact, please.

474
00:28:28,910 --> 00:28:30,280
The fact that
you voted for Jeong Han...

475
00:28:31,250 --> 00:28:33,520
- really hurt my feelings.
- That's because you didn't...

476
00:28:33,520 --> 00:28:34,720
Grandpa, please.

477
00:28:35,390 --> 00:28:36,390
Here.

478
00:28:38,820 --> 00:28:39,820
Okay.

479
00:28:42,330 --> 00:28:43,690
I see.

480
00:28:44,930 --> 00:28:46,000
You did great.

481
00:28:46,360 --> 00:28:49,170
Okay, now it's your turn, Grandpa.
Tell us what upset you.

482
00:28:51,870 --> 00:28:54,040
I went to see a doctor,

483
00:28:54,640 --> 00:28:56,740
but you cared about
which doctor I saw,

484
00:28:56,740 --> 00:28:59,440
and not about what was wrong.

485
00:28:59,710 --> 00:29:02,180
- That really upset me.
- That was...

486
00:29:02,580 --> 00:29:03,580
Here.

487
00:29:08,950 --> 00:29:12,760
I see, so that's how you felt.
That's what upset you.

488
00:29:13,620 --> 00:29:16,230
I'm sorry. It's not that
it didn't occur to me.

489
00:29:16,430 --> 00:29:17,790
I just wasn't myself at that moment.

490
00:29:19,060 --> 00:29:20,900
Okay, now it's your turn
to say what upset you.

491
00:29:23,770 --> 00:29:24,770
Father.

492
00:29:25,270 --> 00:29:26,740
The way you've always...

493
00:29:27,370 --> 00:29:28,940
compared me to Jeong Han
since I was young...

494
00:29:29,640 --> 00:29:32,240
and always calling me
a good-for-nothing.

495
00:29:33,040 --> 00:29:35,350
- It's upsetting.
- I see.

496
00:29:36,510 --> 00:29:39,880
I didn't realize I was doing that.
I apologize.

497
00:29:40,520 --> 00:29:41,520
Okay.

498
00:29:41,950 --> 00:29:44,520
But does that give you the right
to leave your old man to eat alone?

499
00:29:45,520 --> 00:29:47,120
That made me so upset.

500
00:29:50,030 --> 00:29:52,030
I'm sorry.
I didn't realize you felt that way.

501
00:29:52,830 --> 00:29:55,000
Okay, now hold hands.

502
00:29:55,060 --> 00:29:56,570
Come on, give me your hands.

503
00:29:57,070 --> 00:30:01,170
Okay, repeat after me.
"It's all good."

504
00:30:01,640 --> 00:30:04,310
- It's all good...
- It's all good.

505
00:30:04,310 --> 00:30:05,410
Sir.

506
00:30:06,280 --> 00:30:07,340
Please don't do that again.

507
00:30:12,320 --> 00:30:13,320
You did great.

508
00:30:48,120 --> 00:30:52,990
Thank you for the gift.
It really cheered everyone up.

509
00:30:54,520 --> 00:30:55,530
I'm glad to hear that.

510
00:31:01,560 --> 00:31:02,570
Oh, my.

511
00:31:05,300 --> 00:31:07,470
Don't tell me I woke you up.

512
00:31:08,640 --> 00:31:11,570
I just sent it
so you'd see it in the morning.

513
00:31:13,580 --> 00:31:18,380
I couldn't sleep anyway.
Dad and Grandpa are a snoring duo.

514
00:31:21,020 --> 00:31:25,620
I had something to tell you earlier,
but I didn't get the chance.

515
00:31:26,990 --> 00:31:28,120
And what's that?

516
00:31:28,890 --> 00:31:31,360
You're not answering already,
are you?

517
00:31:32,260 --> 00:31:34,800
I'm not going on that blind date
tomorrow.

518
00:31:36,330 --> 00:31:38,740
You told me how you feel,
and I kept you waiting.

519
00:31:38,840 --> 00:31:41,740
So it doesn't feel right
to see someone else.

520
00:31:42,740 --> 00:31:43,810
Thank you.

521
00:31:44,910 --> 00:31:46,780
Good night, then.

522
00:31:51,780 --> 00:31:53,520
What does that mean?

523
00:31:53,980 --> 00:31:55,990
I'll see you in your dreams.

524
00:31:57,290 --> 00:31:58,350
Stay out of my dreams.

525
00:31:59,220 --> 00:32:00,490
Good night, then.

526
00:32:13,870 --> 00:32:14,870
Ten.

527
00:32:15,710 --> 00:32:16,870
Oh, boy.

528
00:32:17,810 --> 00:32:19,140
Be careful, Mom.

529
00:32:20,640 --> 00:32:22,680
Wow, take it easy.
You'll hurt yourself.

530
00:32:24,010 --> 00:32:26,880
- Does it hurt?
- No, I'm fine.

531
00:32:28,520 --> 00:32:30,420
Your hands have gotten so thin.

532
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:32,360
- Look at this.
- Oh, please.

533
00:32:32,360 --> 00:32:33,860
Go down.

534
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:37,860
- Mom, be careful. Easy does it.
- Come on up.

535
00:32:38,130 --> 00:32:39,130
That's it, up you go.

536
00:32:39,530 --> 00:32:44,170
- You did great. Now, go down.
- Way to go, Mom! All the way.

537
00:32:44,230 --> 00:32:47,240
- Now, turn it slowly.
- Five, six, seven.

538
00:33:01,780 --> 00:33:02,850
What is it, Mom?

539
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:04,920
You think that man looks like Dad?

540
00:33:07,120 --> 00:33:11,030
I'm telling you, that other guy
was his spitting image.

541
00:33:11,490 --> 00:33:12,800
Okay, Mom, that's enough.

542
00:33:13,400 --> 00:33:17,170
- No more trips to the police, okay?
- All right, I'll stop.

543
00:33:19,300 --> 00:33:23,240
Man, it's been a while
since the three of us did this.

544
00:33:24,010 --> 00:33:25,010
It really has.

545
00:33:25,270 --> 00:33:27,810
- We should do this more often.
- Yes.

546
00:33:28,140 --> 00:33:29,280
Mom.

547
00:33:29,580 --> 00:33:33,650
Next week marks
our 40th anniversary...

548
00:33:33,720 --> 00:33:35,420
of setting up here
in Onjeong Market.

549
00:33:35,790 --> 00:33:37,690
Forty years?
Has it really been that long?

550
00:33:38,190 --> 00:33:43,160
Our clinic and Dr. Yang's clinic
are the oldest ones in the market.

551
00:33:44,930 --> 00:33:46,560
Forty years already...

552
00:33:57,240 --> 00:34:00,080
Here, dig in.
I kept it simple today.

553
00:34:00,980 --> 00:34:04,510
- Eat up, Father. You too, honey.
- Pasta for breakfast?

554
00:34:06,580 --> 00:34:09,250
Sitting side by side.
Does that mean you two made up?

555
00:34:10,150 --> 00:34:11,150
Sit down.

556
00:34:11,450 --> 00:34:13,760
You seem thrilled
you didn't have to cook today.

557
00:34:13,820 --> 00:34:15,730
Hey, you're on dish duty
for that comment, Eun Bin.

558
00:34:17,730 --> 00:34:20,860
So Ji Hu's at his academy.
Where are my aunt and uncle?

559
00:34:21,160 --> 00:34:23,570
They went out for brunch.

560
00:34:23,900 --> 00:34:25,400
Brunch?

561
00:34:26,140 --> 00:34:28,070
This looks delicious.
Thank you for the meal!

562
00:34:36,250 --> 00:34:38,250
Why are you so dressed up?

563
00:34:38,950 --> 00:34:40,350
What's this about?

564
00:34:41,050 --> 00:34:43,150
I didn't want to look pathetic,
especially not today.

565
00:34:51,560 --> 00:34:52,560
A divorce.

566
00:34:53,230 --> 00:34:54,630
Let's do it.

567
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:56,630
Are you serious?

568
00:34:57,400 --> 00:35:00,170
- There are conditions.
- Anything. Just name them.

569
00:35:00,470 --> 00:35:03,070
You need to work hard
and send child support for Ji Hu.

570
00:35:03,240 --> 00:35:05,940
Of course, I will.
I swear I'll work hard.

571
00:35:06,010 --> 00:35:08,010
On Ji Hu's birthday
and for Christmas,

572
00:35:08,310 --> 00:35:10,210
make sure you send him a gift,
even if it's just a gift card.

573
00:35:11,150 --> 00:35:15,490
You must attend his big events
so he won't feel fatherless.

574
00:35:15,550 --> 00:35:17,520
Okay, yes! What else? Keep going!

575
00:35:18,050 --> 00:35:21,860
I am never going to date
another man.

576
00:35:26,560 --> 00:35:28,130
So when our Ji Hu gets married...

577
00:35:31,530 --> 00:35:33,370
You have to come
and sit in his father's place.

578
00:35:36,710 --> 00:35:37,810
And...

579
00:35:38,880 --> 00:35:41,480
spend at least one week with Ji Hu
before you leave.

580
00:35:43,110 --> 00:35:45,720
About that... Yes, of course.

581
00:35:47,220 --> 00:35:48,920
And when you're with Ji Hu,

582
00:35:49,620 --> 00:35:51,450
don't you dare contact that woman.

583
00:35:53,920 --> 00:35:57,060
Right. Okay, I won't.

584
00:36:19,020 --> 00:36:20,520
So, why were we all called here?

585
00:36:20,920 --> 00:36:22,450
Is there some
big announcement or what?

586
00:36:23,250 --> 00:36:26,620
The thing is...

587
00:36:26,690 --> 00:36:28,690
What trouble did you cause
this time?

588
00:36:29,160 --> 00:36:33,700
- Well, it's...
- I'll explain.

589
00:36:34,860 --> 00:36:38,970
He's leaving for Saudi Arabia
this weekend.

590
00:36:39,070 --> 00:36:41,500
What? Saudi Arabia?
Why, all of a sudden?

591
00:36:42,240 --> 00:36:45,980
Apparently, his friend started
a construction supply business,

592
00:36:46,080 --> 00:36:50,950
and he asked him for help.
It'll probably take a few years.

593
00:36:52,180 --> 00:36:53,720
Why, you...

594
00:36:57,020 --> 00:36:58,890
That's a smart move.

595
00:36:59,260 --> 00:37:00,620
After all your trouble,

596
00:37:01,020 --> 00:37:02,960
you're finally stepping up.

597
00:37:05,600 --> 00:37:07,160
When we were young,
a lot of fathers...

598
00:37:07,160 --> 00:37:08,860
went to Saudi Arabia to make money.

599
00:37:08,970 --> 00:37:12,540
Someone from every other house went.
To Saudi Arabia, Libya,

600
00:37:12,540 --> 00:37:16,340
- and Kuwait!
- Auntie, is this really true?

601
00:37:16,810 --> 00:37:20,510
Yes, of course.
It was a last-minute decision.

602
00:37:20,940 --> 00:37:21,940
So just leave it at that.

603
00:37:22,380 --> 00:37:23,810
Go over there
and make a lot of money.

604
00:37:24,580 --> 00:37:26,420
It's a man's duty
to provide for his wife and kids.

605
00:37:27,120 --> 00:37:28,520
And from now on,
get your life together.

606
00:37:30,220 --> 00:37:31,220
I will.

607
00:37:42,100 --> 00:37:43,670
I'm a little worried about my aunt.

608
00:37:44,170 --> 00:37:46,340
I'll take good care of her.
Don't you worry.

609
00:37:46,770 --> 00:37:49,970
Anyway, you couldn't even rest
on the weekend. Thanks.

610
00:37:50,110 --> 00:37:52,780
I'm so glad your dad and grandpa
made up, thanks to you.

611
00:37:53,210 --> 00:37:56,610
But Dad snores like a log.
Does it bother you at night?

612
00:37:56,680 --> 00:37:58,610
I actually like it.
It's like a lullaby to me.

613
00:38:01,950 --> 00:38:04,190
My gosh. Ji Hu.

614
00:38:17,800 --> 00:38:19,970
What was it like for you
when your parents got divorced?

615
00:38:21,800 --> 00:38:23,370
It was tough.

616
00:38:24,910 --> 00:38:26,340
That's why, as you probably know,

617
00:38:27,140 --> 00:38:28,710
I ran away, pretending
I was going to study abroad.

618
00:38:29,080 --> 00:38:30,510
I had to give up everything I loved.

619
00:38:32,480 --> 00:38:33,480
Do you regret it?

620
00:38:34,780 --> 00:38:35,790
Yes.

621
00:38:36,550 --> 00:38:37,550
That's why...

622
00:38:37,820 --> 00:38:39,990
I'm trying so hard
to get it all back now.

623
00:38:40,960 --> 00:38:41,990
You're talking about a girl?

624
00:38:42,760 --> 00:38:43,760
Yes.

625
00:38:45,160 --> 00:38:47,360
What about you?
You want to study abroad, too?

626
00:38:47,860 --> 00:38:49,900
No, I'm not going to.

627
00:38:50,500 --> 00:38:51,800
I'm going to stick it out here.

628
00:38:52,500 --> 00:38:53,700
To protect your mom?

629
00:38:54,900 --> 00:38:56,140
That's part of it,

630
00:38:56,710 --> 00:38:58,270
but I also don't want
to break up with my girlfriend.

631
00:39:00,010 --> 00:39:01,080
Right.

632
00:39:01,740 --> 00:39:03,210
You're a lot better than I was.

633
00:39:03,810 --> 00:39:05,250
I'm sure
you'll get through it just fine.

634
00:39:06,680 --> 00:39:07,680
I'll try my best.

635
00:39:18,130 --> 00:39:20,260
(Alarm)

636
00:39:23,330 --> 00:39:25,800
Gosh, you're up already?

637
00:39:28,700 --> 00:39:31,940
I have a shoot this week,
so I have a lot to prep.

638
00:39:33,310 --> 00:39:37,980
Have Ju Ah drive for you sometimes.
She always hitches a ride with you.

639
00:39:38,080 --> 00:39:39,920
Ju Ah has it tough, too.

640
00:39:41,950 --> 00:39:43,790
This is all your fault.

641
00:39:44,650 --> 00:39:47,720
Come on. How is this my fault now?
Goodness.

642
00:39:47,860 --> 00:39:50,760
Things would've been so much better
if we'd moved to Seoul like I said!

643
00:39:51,030 --> 00:39:54,200
If we'd moved, your sister-in-law
wouldn't have had an affair.

644
00:39:54,800 --> 00:39:56,430
What? Why? How does that make sense?

645
00:39:56,700 --> 00:39:59,700
What, does her lover live here
in Onjeong or something?

646
00:40:00,700 --> 00:40:02,170
I don't know.

647
00:40:03,070 --> 00:40:08,040
Gosh, I'm just sick and tired of you
constantly fighting with Bucket.

648
00:40:09,040 --> 00:40:11,350
If we'd moved to Seoul,
you would've made more money,

649
00:40:11,710 --> 00:40:13,320
and I wouldn't have had to do
the TV show.

650
00:40:13,820 --> 00:40:16,590
Honestly, how could we have afforded
to move to Seoul?

651
00:40:17,750 --> 00:40:19,020
So if we have the money,
you'll move?

652
00:40:19,660 --> 00:40:21,060
We've paid off our loans,

653
00:40:21,320 --> 00:40:23,260
and I'll be getting paid
once I sign my contract.

654
00:40:23,630 --> 00:40:28,530
Come on, you know clinics are scarce
on the outskirts of Onjeong.

655
00:40:28,600 --> 00:40:30,500
Gosh, there he goes again.

656
00:40:31,500 --> 00:40:35,640
If I leave for Seoul too,
who will care for the market people?

657
00:40:35,700 --> 00:40:40,180
And what younger doctor will want
to come out to the boonies?

658
00:40:40,540 --> 00:40:42,610
Mother needs to get some rest, too.

659
00:40:42,750 --> 00:40:47,820
What? Mom's so young and healthy
because she works.

660
00:40:47,820 --> 00:40:50,490
If she stops working,
she'll age in a heartbeat.

661
00:40:51,190 --> 00:40:53,120
And the rumors about
your brother's divorce...

662
00:40:53,760 --> 00:40:55,260
are going to be
all over the market soon.

663
00:40:55,360 --> 00:40:59,200
So what? Divorce is no big deal.
Besides, Dae Han has no kids.

664
00:40:59,260 --> 00:41:02,260
Frankly, we should spread the rumor
so he can get remarried.

665
00:41:02,400 --> 00:41:05,500
And as the newly elected president,
I'm already swamped.

666
00:41:05,600 --> 00:41:09,540
- What do you mean, move?
- Gosh, I can't even look at you.

667
00:41:10,170 --> 00:41:11,670
- Go on, go back to sleep.
- What?

668
00:41:12,070 --> 00:41:14,240
You know what?
I think I will sleep a little more.

669
00:41:15,240 --> 00:41:20,220
- You smell nice.
- Gosh, get away from me.

670
00:41:21,920 --> 00:41:23,720
Did you want to talk to me
about something?

671
00:41:25,590 --> 00:41:26,590
What is it?

672
00:41:27,690 --> 00:41:32,390
The reason you lost the election
isn't that I didn't vote for you.

673
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:34,000
I know.

674
00:41:34,760 --> 00:41:39,100
- Because Jeong Han was better?
- No. People just dislike you.

675
00:41:40,240 --> 00:41:42,100
Oh, I see.

676
00:41:43,570 --> 00:41:46,640
No, he's not saying
that you're unlikable.

677
00:41:46,910 --> 00:41:49,810
He just means
you're perceived as unlikable.

678
00:41:50,080 --> 00:41:53,550
When you hear even dogs hate you,
that's something you have to fix.

679
00:41:53,780 --> 00:41:55,120
We can't have
Councilor Hwang's people...

680
00:41:55,120 --> 00:41:56,650
hearing rumors like that.

681
00:41:57,150 --> 00:41:58,150
Exactly.

682
00:41:58,820 --> 00:42:02,520
Dr. Gong has already solidified
his reputation as a friendly guy.

683
00:42:02,760 --> 00:42:04,790
So, compared
to the association's president,

684
00:42:04,860 --> 00:42:07,930
you need an image as vice president
who's more proactive.

685
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:09,770
That's how you'll earn
people's trust.

686
00:42:11,030 --> 00:42:13,170
That's my girl, Se Ri.
That's exactly my point.

687
00:42:14,070 --> 00:42:17,010
A VP who's more proactive
than the president.

688
00:42:17,640 --> 00:42:19,240
What do you think, honey?
You can do it, right?

689
00:42:22,040 --> 00:42:23,910
- One, two, three, four.
- One, two, three, four.

690
00:42:24,380 --> 00:42:27,350
- Five, six, seven, eight.
- Five, six, seven, eight.

691
00:42:27,420 --> 00:42:29,990
- Two, two, three, four.
- Two, two, three, four.

692
00:42:30,390 --> 00:42:32,920
- Five, six, seven, eight.
- Five, six, seven, eight.

693
00:42:32,990 --> 00:42:35,320
Okay, leg forward
and make a finger heart, all right?

694
00:42:35,520 --> 00:42:40,030
One, two, three, four.
Now, blow it to your partner.

695
00:42:40,200 --> 00:42:44,100
Seven, eight. Switch feet.
Two, two, three, four.

696
00:42:44,170 --> 00:42:48,000
Bigger smiles, everyone!
One, two, seven, eight.

697
00:42:48,070 --> 00:42:49,970
Great. All right,
shall we do some hip rotations?

698
00:42:50,810 --> 00:42:54,480
All right, great work, everyone.

699
00:42:55,180 --> 00:43:00,120
- All right, let's have another...
- Have a healthy and profitable day!

700
00:43:00,320 --> 00:43:03,350
See you all again tomorrow.
See you tomorrow!

701
00:43:04,050 --> 00:43:08,190
I'm going to finish cleaning up
around Onjeong Market,

702
00:43:08,420 --> 00:43:10,330
and then
I will start my clinic hours.

703
00:43:10,960 --> 00:43:14,960
All right, dismissed!
I hope you all get rich!

704
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:16,770
Yes!

705
00:43:17,770 --> 00:43:22,500
All right. Oh, man.
Why so much trash everywhere?

706
00:43:23,110 --> 00:43:26,410
<i>The sun's up in the sky</i>

707
00:43:28,710 --> 00:43:29,710
What's gotten into him?

708
00:43:30,280 --> 00:43:31,680
What's with
the sudden change of attitude?

709
00:43:32,010 --> 00:43:33,820
A sudden change in character
means you're about to die.

710
00:43:33,820 --> 00:43:36,790
(Onjeong Market)

711
00:43:37,190 --> 00:43:40,420
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

712
00:43:43,290 --> 00:43:45,790
The situation appears resolved,
thanks to our initial containment.

713
00:43:45,860 --> 00:43:47,930
No, we don't know that for sure.

714
00:43:48,430 --> 00:43:50,400
They say to always check for embers.

715
00:43:51,100 --> 00:43:52,100
Right.

716
00:43:57,110 --> 00:43:59,840
Oh, I heard Dr. Yang's sister
is also getting a divorce.

717
00:44:00,910 --> 00:44:02,540
That's a relief.

718
00:44:03,050 --> 00:44:04,680
I was worried
Hui Gyeong would cause a scene...

719
00:44:04,680 --> 00:44:06,480
if that man couldn't get a divorce.

720
00:44:07,350 --> 00:44:10,620
Wait, are you telling them
all of our family business?

721
00:44:11,650 --> 00:44:15,460
No, of course not.
It was just an emergency situation,

722
00:44:15,820 --> 00:44:17,260
so we were just
exchanging information.

723
00:44:17,790 --> 00:44:19,600
All for the sake of peace
between both families.

724
00:44:20,200 --> 00:44:24,500
Oh, dear. Anyway, I'm just so glad
it all blew over quietly.

725
00:44:25,070 --> 00:44:26,070
Tell me about it.

726
00:44:28,770 --> 00:44:29,770
I'm exhausted.

727
00:44:30,970 --> 00:44:34,610
I get tired
just thinking about the TV shoot.

728
00:44:35,810 --> 00:44:39,820
Mom, have you gotten any offers
for commercials or anything?

729
00:44:40,450 --> 00:44:43,950
It seems like all the doctors on TV
are doing commercials these days.

730
00:44:44,020 --> 00:44:47,590
Oh, please.
The show is already killing me.

731
00:44:47,920 --> 00:44:48,920
Why do you ask?

732
00:44:49,390 --> 00:44:50,960
It's nothing, just wondering.

733
00:44:51,630 --> 00:44:54,800
Anyway,
stay away from Bucket's kids.

734
00:44:55,730 --> 00:44:58,730
Astrologically speaking,
our families are incompatible.

735
00:44:59,900 --> 00:45:01,770
What kind of doctor
says something like that?

736
00:45:02,140 --> 00:45:04,910
- With no proof.
- What do you mean there's no proof?

737
00:45:05,310 --> 00:45:08,780
The energy of the unconscious
causes transference and compulsion,

738
00:45:08,840 --> 00:45:13,450
and even Freud wrote a paper
on how that twists relationships.

739
00:45:14,550 --> 00:45:16,050
Anyway,
just don't get close to them.

740
00:45:16,320 --> 00:45:17,320
Got it?

741
00:45:18,090 --> 00:45:21,890
Why would I?
I hardly see them anyway.

742
00:45:22,690 --> 00:45:23,760
My gosh.

743
00:45:28,760 --> 00:45:30,600
You know this is the third time
we're reviewing this, right?

744
00:45:31,270 --> 00:45:34,970
Right. So no typos,
and the image cuts are fine.

745
00:45:35,840 --> 00:45:36,840
Go ahead and send it.

746
00:45:37,240 --> 00:45:39,510
- Really? Okay.
- Yes.

747
00:45:42,410 --> 00:45:43,750
(Email sent successfully.)

748
00:45:45,050 --> 00:45:46,080
Sent!

749
00:45:47,120 --> 00:45:49,550
I really hope it goes well.

750
00:45:51,620 --> 00:45:55,060
Right. I'll make your mother
a formal modeling offer.

751
00:45:56,630 --> 00:45:59,360
You'd probably save time
looking for another model.

752
00:45:59,660 --> 00:46:00,700
She'll turn you down.

753
00:46:01,400 --> 00:46:03,170
But I really wish
she would be our model.

754
00:46:04,000 --> 00:46:05,200
Why do you care so much?

755
00:46:06,140 --> 00:46:10,310
Your mother wearing your designs
and walking the opening runway,

756
00:46:10,610 --> 00:46:13,910
and you two bowing at the finale...
I think that would be wonderful.

757
00:46:21,950 --> 00:46:23,590
That does sound nice.

758
00:46:24,550 --> 00:46:25,690
She won't do it, though.

759
00:46:27,160 --> 00:46:29,660
Leave that to the company.
We'll handle it.

760
00:46:33,060 --> 00:46:34,960
(Taehan)

761
00:46:35,330 --> 00:46:36,570
Good morning.

762
00:46:37,270 --> 00:46:38,270
What?

763
00:46:39,230 --> 00:46:40,470
What is all this?

764
00:46:42,240 --> 00:46:44,410
An atelier, just for you.

765
00:46:45,710 --> 00:46:48,780
I was worried helping with marketing
would keep you from your real work,

766
00:46:49,610 --> 00:46:51,810
so I spruced this place up
to help you stay inspired.

767
00:46:52,650 --> 00:46:53,680
Do you like it?

768
00:46:57,520 --> 00:46:58,520
I absolutely love it.

769
00:47:00,120 --> 00:47:01,390
Oh, my.

770
00:47:05,960 --> 00:47:06,960
This is amazing.

771
00:47:17,570 --> 00:47:22,510
Okay, these two outfits are
our final entries for the contest,

772
00:47:22,880 --> 00:47:26,480
and if we get the platform deal,
they'll be our main design samples.

773
00:47:27,350 --> 00:47:28,550
The execution is good,

774
00:47:29,120 --> 00:47:30,890
and the brand image
is sophisticated,

775
00:47:31,290 --> 00:47:33,360
Overall, the quality is outstanding.

776
00:47:33,760 --> 00:47:34,790
Is there...

777
00:47:35,020 --> 00:47:37,290
any word from the platform yet?

778
00:47:38,060 --> 00:47:40,260
Pacu Nacho,
you haven't told them yet?

779
00:47:42,700 --> 00:47:45,200
The proposal we submitted
to Hyegyeong Department Store...

780
00:47:46,540 --> 00:47:48,800
received a very positive evaluation,
thanks to Ms. Gong Ju Ah.

781
00:47:51,610 --> 00:47:54,980
Now, if we win the contest
and secure the company's funding,

782
00:47:55,710 --> 00:47:59,510
Entry into Hyegyeong will be smooth,
and our brand image will improve.

783
00:47:59,880 --> 00:48:02,250
So are we really
getting into Hyegyeong?

784
00:48:03,220 --> 00:48:05,590
It's a bit early
to pop the champagne,

785
00:48:06,390 --> 00:48:09,460
but there's nothing sweeter
than popping it a little early.

786
00:48:10,590 --> 00:48:13,060
- Wow, look at that marbling.
- The meat quality is unreal.

787
00:48:13,130 --> 00:48:15,530
Everyone, fill up your glasses.

788
00:48:16,000 --> 00:48:19,570
To Pacu Nacho and Ms. Gong
for their hard work on the proposal.

789
00:48:20,040 --> 00:48:23,240
All right,
shall we toast with our slogan?

790
00:48:23,640 --> 00:48:24,640
Shall we?

791
00:48:25,240 --> 00:48:29,280
- Return to FG!
- Return to FG!

792
00:48:30,680 --> 00:48:33,120
- Great work, everyone!
- Well done!

793
00:48:33,180 --> 00:48:36,450
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

794
00:48:37,620 --> 00:48:39,120
Wow, the food here is so good.

795
00:48:40,290 --> 00:48:42,660
He really is handsome.

796
00:48:42,820 --> 00:48:47,600
- Those forearms. So sexy.
- Like this, you know?

797
00:48:48,800 --> 00:48:51,230
What are you two whispering about?
Let me in on it.

798
00:48:52,630 --> 00:48:54,740
All the women on the marketing team
these days...

799
00:48:55,970 --> 00:48:58,840
- are swooning over the Director.
- Let's do this more often.

800
00:48:58,940 --> 00:49:00,680
The VP must be thrilled.

801
00:49:02,210 --> 00:49:03,910
- Should I grill the meat?
- No, it's fine.

802
00:49:03,980 --> 00:49:05,810
- Are you sure? Really?
- Yes.

803
00:49:07,220 --> 00:49:11,820
Here, eat something with that.
Don't drink on an empty stomach, VP.

804
00:49:12,120 --> 00:49:13,120
I'm fine.

805
00:49:13,520 --> 00:49:15,160
Why don't you take care
of someone over there?

806
00:49:16,290 --> 00:49:17,290
Come on.

807
00:49:17,660 --> 00:49:19,330
Vice President,
let me pour you a drink.

808
00:49:22,030 --> 00:49:23,930
You must be very worried
about the Chairman.

809
00:49:24,330 --> 00:49:26,030
It's the Chairman
who's worried about me.

810
00:49:26,640 --> 00:49:28,040
That's why he's holding on.

811
00:49:30,240 --> 00:49:33,680
The moment my father passes,
many people will come after me.

812
00:49:35,110 --> 00:49:37,080
It's a breath of fresh air
coming to the Fashion Division.

813
00:49:37,380 --> 00:49:40,380
- Thanks for letting me join.
- Of course. You're welcome anytime.

814
00:49:41,820 --> 00:49:43,920
- By the way, Mr. Park.
- Yes?

815
00:49:44,950 --> 00:49:45,950
Ms. Gong.

816
00:49:52,030 --> 00:49:53,530
Don't they look like they're dating?

817
00:49:57,200 --> 00:49:59,370
Director, have some of this too.

818
00:49:59,870 --> 00:50:00,870
Thanks.

819
00:50:05,010 --> 00:50:07,140
Shouldn't we just wait and see?

820
00:50:08,280 --> 00:50:09,280
This is so exciting.

821
00:50:09,910 --> 00:50:11,950
Lately, watching those two
is the highlight of my day at work.

822
00:50:38,510 --> 00:50:39,640
I've been looking all over for you.

823
00:50:40,410 --> 00:50:42,240
Why are you here all by yourself?

824
00:50:43,710 --> 00:50:48,120
Well, drinking always gives me
the munchies for carbs.

825
00:50:54,720 --> 00:50:57,930
- Dipping bread in the soup?
- What? Yes.

826
00:50:58,230 --> 00:50:59,230
Like fondue.

827
00:50:59,460 --> 00:51:03,430
And when you're done with that,
you'll crush cookies in ice cream.

828
00:51:04,730 --> 00:51:07,400
Wow, you remember everything.

829
00:51:08,140 --> 00:51:10,210
You used to say
I had the weirdest food cravings.

830
00:51:12,510 --> 00:51:15,540
Did your uncle get to the concert?
It's today.

831
00:51:15,810 --> 00:51:18,280
Yes, he's sent me lots of pictures.
He's having a blast.

832
00:51:18,810 --> 00:51:19,980
Thank you so much.

833
00:51:20,720 --> 00:51:24,150
Oh, right. Father...
I mean, your father...

834
00:51:24,250 --> 00:51:26,220
I mean, Dr. Yang.

835
00:51:27,690 --> 00:51:30,360
You have a lot of names for him.
What about my dad?

836
00:51:30,990 --> 00:51:34,930
I heard Dr. Yang
has been working really hard lately.

837
00:51:35,200 --> 00:51:37,070
Yes, so I've heard.

838
00:51:37,870 --> 00:51:41,670
A project to fix his bad image,
or so they say.

839
00:51:51,780 --> 00:51:52,810
All right.

840
00:51:54,250 --> 00:51:55,550
Take Gopyeong Market.

841
00:51:56,120 --> 00:51:59,090
After opening its night market,
tourism soared,

842
00:51:59,190 --> 00:52:01,720
and sales tripled.

843
00:52:03,830 --> 00:52:06,760
But our goal for Onjeong Market...

844
00:52:07,530 --> 00:52:09,630
is a whopping fivefold increase
in sales.

845
00:52:12,430 --> 00:52:15,270
I'm serious, everyone.
A fivefold increase.

846
00:52:16,640 --> 00:52:18,940
More customers would be great
for us, of course.

847
00:52:19,270 --> 00:52:22,310
- That would be amazing.
- Yes, totally.

848
00:52:23,450 --> 00:52:25,310
- He's going overboard.
- All right.

849
00:52:25,710 --> 00:52:27,720
- He's really laying it on thick.
- So, what's the first step?

850
00:52:28,120 --> 00:52:29,720
We need to establish
the infrastructure.

851
00:52:30,220 --> 00:52:34,220
Right? You all know this.
Second, accessibility...

852
00:52:34,720 --> 00:52:39,090
All right, tell me your problems.
I, Yang Dong Ik, will solve them.

853
00:52:39,260 --> 00:52:40,260
Go on, speak up.

854
00:52:40,630 --> 00:52:43,400
- The dumpsters are too far away.
- Okay.

855
00:52:43,470 --> 00:52:45,830
- It's so hard to get to every time.
- I'm sure that's been difficult.

856
00:52:45,900 --> 00:52:50,570
- Yes.
- A central waste disposal area.

857
00:52:51,010 --> 00:52:52,870
Look into installing
an additional one.

858
00:52:53,170 --> 00:52:55,710
- Okay, next.
- There isn't enough parking.

859
00:52:55,710 --> 00:52:56,850
We need more parking spaces.

860
00:52:56,910 --> 00:52:58,080
You're right. We need that.

861
00:52:58,350 --> 00:53:01,980
Okay. A public parking lot nearby.
Done.

862
00:53:01,980 --> 00:53:03,720
- Please add more restrooms.
- Of course! We need those.

863
00:53:03,790 --> 00:53:05,790
- Can you help promote our market?
- Promoting is my specialty.

864
00:53:06,020 --> 00:53:07,460
Please set up
a lounge for the merchants.

865
00:53:07,460 --> 00:53:08,960
- That's right.
- You don't have one?

866
00:53:09,020 --> 00:53:10,090
- Sure, we'll do it.
- Please make it happen.

867
00:53:10,890 --> 00:53:11,890
Thank you.

868
00:53:17,230 --> 00:53:21,500
- Ji Hu's Dad is home.
- He is?

869
00:53:22,200 --> 00:53:23,200
Thank goodness.

870
00:53:23,940 --> 00:53:24,940
Tell me about it.

871
00:53:25,810 --> 00:53:27,980
I guess I had it all wrong.

872
00:53:28,810 --> 00:53:29,810
That's good.

873
00:53:32,010 --> 00:53:33,280
I've decided to get a divorce.

874
00:53:37,420 --> 00:53:38,590
But...

875
00:53:39,090 --> 00:53:42,090
do you know who your wife
had an affair with?

876
00:53:43,390 --> 00:53:44,390
I don't know.

877
00:53:44,830 --> 00:53:46,830
What good would it do to know?
It would only hurt more.

878
00:53:50,070 --> 00:53:53,870
No way. It can't be.
This is ridiculous.

879
00:53:56,340 --> 00:53:57,340
What's wrong?

880
00:53:58,070 --> 00:54:00,240
It's nothing.

881
00:54:14,690 --> 00:54:15,690
Oh, dear.

882
00:54:24,900 --> 00:54:27,570
- Oh, Mother.
- Hey.

883
00:54:29,540 --> 00:54:33,310
Are you reviewing your script
for the shoot today?

884
00:54:33,480 --> 00:54:36,280
Yes. Why are you up so early?

885
00:54:37,110 --> 00:54:39,480
- Did my light wake you?
- No.

886
00:54:39,810 --> 00:54:42,580
No, I just had a nightmare,

887
00:54:42,980 --> 00:54:44,920
and I felt so stifled.

888
00:54:45,950 --> 00:54:49,220
It's chilly. Go back inside.
Let me get you some tea. Okay?

889
00:54:49,290 --> 00:54:50,290
All right.

890
00:54:56,000 --> 00:54:57,000
What's wrong, Mother?

891
00:55:03,840 --> 00:55:05,410
Let's get rid of that.

892
00:55:08,040 --> 00:55:09,940
Yes, let's.

893
00:55:10,680 --> 00:55:11,910
I can't believe
I didn't think of that.

894
00:55:23,560 --> 00:55:25,630
The call cannot be connected.
You'll be connected to voicemail...

895
00:55:48,180 --> 00:55:50,090
(Hui)

896
00:55:50,150 --> 00:55:51,720
(Missed Call: Hui)

897
00:55:58,390 --> 00:56:00,660
- Hello?
- You'll be connected to...

898
00:56:05,830 --> 00:56:09,170
Don't delude yourself into thinking
he's going to love you forever.

899
00:56:09,800 --> 00:56:13,740
He might be sweet to you now,
caught in the thrill of the affair,

900
00:56:14,140 --> 00:56:16,140
but will he be responsible...

901
00:56:16,580 --> 00:56:18,180
when he's married with a child?

902
00:56:21,680 --> 00:56:22,680
No...

903
00:56:30,930 --> 00:56:32,530
My gosh.

904
00:56:32,530 --> 00:56:36,100
I was waiting all week
to hear about the brunch, ma'am.

905
00:56:39,430 --> 00:56:40,540
This...

906
00:56:41,500 --> 00:56:43,000
I feel a little funny taking this.

907
00:56:43,840 --> 00:56:45,340
Councilor Hwang's wife said...

908
00:56:45,340 --> 00:56:47,710
she feels uncomfortable
about you joining us.

909
00:56:52,310 --> 00:56:53,750
I wonder why.

910
00:56:54,920 --> 00:56:57,290
You'd think
she would at least tell me why.

911
00:56:59,290 --> 00:57:02,860
At the brunch,
their daughter came along,

912
00:57:03,160 --> 00:57:04,660
and I remembered
how you once said...

913
00:57:05,030 --> 00:57:07,630
you wanted to set her up
with your son,

914
00:57:08,060 --> 00:57:11,400
so I just casually asked
if she'd be up for a blind date.

915
00:57:12,830 --> 00:57:15,770
And Councilor Hwang's wife
just flew off the handle.

916
00:57:15,770 --> 00:57:17,740
My gosh, why?

917
00:57:18,470 --> 00:57:21,980
Because you're Dr. Yang's
second wife. She doesn't like that.

918
00:57:22,380 --> 00:57:23,650
She was dead serious about it.

919
00:57:28,150 --> 00:57:29,180
So, you're saying...

920
00:57:31,190 --> 00:57:33,860
It's not because of my husband...

921
00:57:35,690 --> 00:57:37,260
It's because of me?

922
00:57:37,760 --> 00:57:38,760
Yes.

923
00:57:39,160 --> 00:57:41,100
What Councilor Hwang
values above all else...

924
00:57:41,360 --> 00:57:42,930
is the wife's standing.

925
00:57:43,300 --> 00:57:45,370
The reason he's trying so hard
to get in with Dr. Gong...

926
00:57:45,830 --> 00:57:47,040
is because of his wife.

927
00:57:58,280 --> 00:58:01,280
You know her, right?
Dr. Han Seong Mi from TV.

928
00:58:02,120 --> 00:58:04,120
She's a local celebrity in Onjeong.

929
00:58:05,250 --> 00:58:08,060
Frankly, you're a housewife
and a second wife.

930
00:58:08,160 --> 00:58:10,020
You can't compare.

931
00:58:32,280 --> 00:58:33,620
We've been running into each other
a lot lately.

932
00:58:34,750 --> 00:58:37,620
I have a show to tape
this afternoon,

933
00:58:37,820 --> 00:58:39,990
so I'm getting my hair done
before heading to the studio.

934
00:58:42,860 --> 00:58:45,060
So, are you transitioning
into a full-time TV doctor?

935
00:58:45,860 --> 00:58:48,560
Then again,
from what I saw in Ganghwa,

936
00:58:49,130 --> 00:58:50,700
you really know
how to put on a show.

937
00:58:51,800 --> 00:58:53,200
Excuse me? A show?

938
00:58:54,070 --> 00:58:55,170
See you around.

939
00:58:58,540 --> 00:58:59,770
Gosh, that woman.

940
00:59:01,610 --> 00:59:03,340
We're just like oil and water.

941
00:59:08,620 --> 00:59:09,620
I will...

942
00:59:09,950 --> 00:59:12,190
drive her out of Onjeong for good.

943
00:59:15,120 --> 00:59:17,790
(Taehan Group)

944
00:59:21,930 --> 00:59:23,600
Wow! Who is this?

945
00:59:24,270 --> 00:59:27,540
Your bestie.
I'm having lunch out today.

946
00:59:28,870 --> 00:59:32,770
Where are you having lunch
all dressed up? What's the occasion?

947
00:59:46,120 --> 00:59:47,820
You're not upset that...

948
00:59:47,820 --> 00:59:49,990
I'm treating you to pork cutlets,
are you?

949
00:59:51,730 --> 00:59:54,960
Did you forget?
Pork cutlets are my favorite.

950
00:59:58,370 --> 01:00:02,770
So, what did you want to discuss
over lunch?

951
01:00:05,170 --> 01:00:06,870
About what you asked me last time...

952
01:00:07,580 --> 01:00:09,240
I'm ready to give you
my answer today.

953
01:00:22,190 --> 01:00:23,730
(Taxi)

954
01:00:28,060 --> 01:00:30,300
Oh, no.
What is she doing here again?

955
01:00:37,970 --> 01:00:39,640
You look so beautiful today.

956
01:00:41,280 --> 01:00:45,610
On an important day,
a woman dresses up for herself.

957
01:00:47,650 --> 01:00:49,520
After getting my hopes up like this,

958
01:00:50,450 --> 01:00:52,920
you're not about to turn me down,
are you?

959
01:01:07,970 --> 01:01:10,810
What's all this?
You all came out to see me off?

960
01:01:11,540 --> 01:01:14,080
- Have a safe trip, Uncle.
- Yes, thanks.

961
01:01:16,480 --> 01:01:17,610
I'm off, honey.

962
01:01:18,080 --> 01:01:19,110
Okay.

963
01:01:21,020 --> 01:01:22,220
I'm off, Father.

964
01:01:22,820 --> 01:01:24,120
Here's some spending money.

965
01:01:24,750 --> 01:01:27,220
And call Dong Suk
the minute you land in Saudi Arabia.

966
01:01:28,460 --> 01:01:30,160
Wow, thank you so much.

967
01:01:32,390 --> 01:01:35,800
You get to Saudi Arabia tomorrow,
Korea time, right?

968
01:01:37,700 --> 01:01:38,700
Yes.

969
01:01:39,530 --> 01:01:40,540
Yes.

970
01:01:41,040 --> 01:01:42,040
Saudi Arabia?

971
01:01:45,510 --> 01:01:47,540
What the...
Isn't that Gong Dae Han's wife?

972
01:01:49,080 --> 01:01:51,380
Are you abandoning me
and going to Saudi Arabia?

973
01:01:52,010 --> 01:01:55,280
You were just going to leave me
and run off like that, darling?

974
01:01:55,350 --> 01:01:56,620
- No, it's not like that...
- "Darling?"

975
01:01:56,680 --> 01:01:57,920
- It's not like that.
- Excuse me.

976
01:01:58,150 --> 01:01:59,190
Hey, you!

977
01:01:59,650 --> 01:02:01,460
- Hui Gyeong.
- I...

978
01:02:01,560 --> 01:02:04,230
- What are you doing? Let's go.
- No...

979
01:02:04,460 --> 01:02:05,460
Wait a minute.

980
01:02:06,230 --> 01:02:07,260
Hold on.

981
01:02:07,800 --> 01:02:09,330
What did you just say to him?

982
01:02:09,930 --> 01:02:10,930
"Darling?"

983
01:02:11,130 --> 01:02:14,370
It's not what you think, Dong Suk.
What're you doing? Go on, take her!

984
01:02:14,440 --> 01:02:15,500
What in the world is going on?

985
01:02:15,840 --> 01:02:19,510
So much drama! Grandpa,
my eyes are about to pop out.

986
01:02:19,640 --> 01:02:22,480
Eun Bin, take Grandfather inside
right now. Hurry.

987
01:02:22,540 --> 01:02:24,850
- Let's go talk somewhere else.
- Let go of me!

988
01:02:25,380 --> 01:02:29,720
I'm not going anywhere without you.
Darling, say something!

989
01:02:29,820 --> 01:02:32,820
- No, it's not... Look.
- Hey!

990
01:02:35,320 --> 01:02:37,090
So the witch having an affair
with my husband...

991
01:02:38,290 --> 01:02:40,030
was you? Gong Dae Han's wife?

992
01:02:42,330 --> 01:02:43,400
That's right. It was me!

993
01:02:43,830 --> 01:02:46,430
I'm the one
your husband really loves.

994
01:02:47,700 --> 01:02:48,700
Shut it!

995
01:02:50,200 --> 01:02:51,710
Nice one, Auntie!

996
01:02:53,170 --> 01:02:55,910
Darling! Are you okay?

997
01:02:56,540 --> 01:02:58,780
- Hey!
- Goodness, this is a disaster.

998
01:02:58,850 --> 01:03:00,050
- You witch.
- Let go!

999
01:03:00,210 --> 01:03:03,150
Only one of us
is walking away from this.

1000
01:03:03,450 --> 01:03:05,150
- I'm going to kill them both!
- Don't!

1001
01:03:05,350 --> 01:03:08,460
- I'm going to kill you both today!
- Stop it!

1002
01:03:08,520 --> 01:03:09,660
Please, stop.

1003
01:03:13,860 --> 01:03:15,100
Goodness. Oh, no.

1004
01:03:16,000 --> 01:03:17,000
I can't believe this...

1005
01:03:47,560 --> 01:03:50,460
(Recipe For Love)

1006
01:03:50,570 --> 01:03:53,130
Is it true your husband's having
an affair with Gong Dae Han's wife?

1007
01:03:53,630 --> 01:03:56,100
Hey! Gong Jeong Han! Gong Dae Han!
Get out here!

1008
01:03:56,100 --> 01:03:58,840
- I'll go out. You stay put.
- Feel better now?

1009
01:03:58,940 --> 01:04:01,880
I have to blame someone,
or I feel like I'm going to die.

1010
01:04:03,910 --> 01:04:07,820
Where did you drag her from?
I want to kill that jerk.

1011
01:04:08,650 --> 01:04:13,150
I went to a good psychic. She said
to stay away from the Gongs.

1012
01:04:13,220 --> 01:04:14,220
The Gongs?

1013
01:04:14,290 --> 01:04:17,830
I'm so worried that our kids
are going to get dragged into this.

1014
01:04:17,890 --> 01:04:21,030
I will never let that happen.

1015
01:04:21,200 --> 01:04:24,130
It's best for our two families
to part ways, right?

1016
01:04:24,570 --> 01:04:27,130
It's time to finally break
this toxic connection.
